# Test Analysis: process_process_table

## Source: process_table.h.spec.md
## Test Report: test_suite_process_process_table.c.report

---

## Summary of Failures

All 10 test cases failed. The root cause is traced to bugs in
`add_process_to__process_table` in `process_table.c`.

---

## Failure Analysis

### Failure 1 — Line 57
**Assertion:** `get_quantity_of__processes_in__process_table(&table) == 1 (0 == 1)`
**Root Cause:**
`add_process_to__process_table` has a logic error when the priority entry is
empty. After calling `initialize_process_priority_table_entry`, it returns
`true` without ever calling
`add_process_to__process_priorty_table_entry_in__ptr_array_of__processes`.
The process is never actually inserted into the pointer array, so the count
remains 0.

